<br>
Not really all that true anymore, in most circumstances.  A Knight can tank in most situations just about as well as a Warrior, barring a significant difference in level or gear.  It used to be they held agro better as well, although with recent changes to the agro from Shadow Knights spells, I'm not sure thats true anymore.  Paladins should still be able to hold agro with stuns though.<br>
<br>
Warriors have a small edge in the 50s because their HP edge is still pretty significant.  But that's really their only major advantage.  And it dwindles pretty rapidly with superior gear and high end buffs.<br>
<br>
I know, I know, you're just repeating the traditional belief.  And I don't fault you for that.  For a long time it was true, but no longer.<br>
<br>
Luckily we still manage to out tank Rangers and Rogues, for the most part.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A> at: 10/2/02 8:31:10 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uluckymike8383.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luckymike8383</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 7:55:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4041.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Pansy Pallies</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all of your help guys.<br>
